Laravel Directory/Application Structure & Artisan (Full Concept Guide)
🔷 1. Laravel Directory Structure (Application Structure)

When you create a Laravel project, it generates a well-organized MVC-based folder structure.

Example:

myapp/

📁 1. app/ (Main Application Logic)

This is the core of your application.

Contains:
Models
Controllers
Middleware
Jobs
Events
Important folders:
app/Http/Controllers   → Business logic (controllers)
app/Models             → Database tables (models)
app/Http/Middleware    → Request filters


👉 Example:

UserController handles login logic
User model handles user table
📁 2. bootstrap/
Initializes the Laravel framework
Loads configuration files
Contains cache files

👉 Rarely modified by developers

📁 3. config/
Stores all configuration settings

Examples:

database.php → DB settings
app.php → app settings
mail.php → email configuration

👉 Very important for system setup

📁 4. database/

Handles database-related work:

Contains:
Migrations (table structure)
Seeders (dummy data)
Factories (test data generation)
📁 5. public/ ⭐ (Entry Point)

This is the main entry of Laravel application

Contains:
index.php (main file)
CSS, JS, images

👉 Browser directly accesses this folder

📁 6. resources/

Used for frontend files

Contains:
views/ → Blade templates (HTML files)
js/ → JavaScript
css/ → Stylesheets

👉 Example:

resources/views/home.blade.php

📁 7. routes/

Defines all URLs of the application

Important files:
web.php → web routes
api.php → API routes
console.php → CLI routes
Example:
Route::get('/home', function () {
    return view('home');
});

📁 8. storage/

Stores:

Logs
Cache
Uploaded files
📁 9. vendor/
Contains all Composer dependencies
Laravel core files also here

👉 Do NOT modify manually

⭐ Laravel Request Flow (Very Important)
User Request → public/index.php → routes → controller → model → view → response

🔷 2. What is Artisan?
⭐ Definition:

Artisan is Laravel’s built-in Command Line Interface (CLI) used to automate repetitive tasks.

👉 It helps developers generate code, manage database, run server, etc.

🔧 3. Why Artisan is used?
To reduce manual coding
To automate tasks
To generate boilerplate code
To manage database easily
To improve development speed
🔷 4. How Artisan Works

Artisan runs via terminal:

php artisan command-name


It interacts with Laravel core to perform tasks.

🔥 5. Important Artisan Commands
🚀 Run server
php artisan serve

🧱 Create Controller
php artisan make:controller UserController

🧠 Create Model
php artisan make:model Product

🗄️ Database migration
php artisan migrate

🧪 Create migration file
php artisan make:migration create_users_table

🌱 Run seeders
php artisan db:seed

🔄 Clear cache
php artisan cache:clear

📋 List all commands
php artisan list

🔷 6. Custom Artisan Commands (Advanced Concept)

You can create your own commands:

php artisan make:command SendEmails


Then define logic inside command class.

🔷 7. Real-Life Analogy

Think of Laravel:

🏗️ Structure = Building
app/ = rooms (logic)
routes/ = doors (URLs)
resources/ = interior design (UI)
database/ = storage system
⚙️ Artisan = Construction machine
Builds controllers
Creates models
Runs database setup
⭐ 8. Advantages of Artisan

✔ Saves time
✔ Automates repetitive tasks
✔ Reduces human error
✔ Fast development
✔ Built-in tooling

⚠️ 9. Limitations

❌ Requires terminal knowledge
❌ Beginners may find commands confusing
❌ Too many commands to remember

⭐ Final Summary
🔷 Laravel Structure:

Laravel follows a strict MVC-based folder system:

app → logic
routes → URLs
resources → UI
database → data
public → entry point
🔷 Artisan:

👉 Artisan is Laravel’s CLI tool used to:

Generate code
Run server
Manage databa
